i think "No money had been transferred" is kind of redundant. 
&nbsp;
"Any length and combination of code **that can be said** to originate" i think this is too broad.
&nbsp;
"Nobody is allowed to add,
change nor remove intellectual property restrictions nor
copyright reservations to fixes, forks, copies,
modifications nor redistributions of code originating from
4Kave derivatives nor the original 4Kave site"
&nbsp;
for some reason this line is bothering me. it seems to imply that the only actions that violates this are fix, fork, copy, while i can't think of anything else, is there any other form of "usage"??
&nbsp;
i'm trying to think of anything else, but quite honestly i have no idea.

@Styromaniac: it's not like you have to sue, its up to you to sue, but as i said, i don't think you can forfeit your right to sue provisionally or indefinitely (in a license).
&nbsp;
however, you can change the language to infer your desire to respect the license and not sue and yet do as you wish if any infringement takes places, something along the lines of:
&nbsp;
"4Kave's original creator is also equally and permanently bound to the terms of this license, violation of these terms are bound to the creator's whim and desires of manifestation that does not involve the act of pursue of license infringement..."
&nbsp;
something like that lol, i think its too broad yet, but its workable.

